At least a dozen people have drowned at lagoons and beaches across the Western Cape in the space of a week. CAPE TOWN - The search continues for a four-year-old boy swept out to sea by strong rip currents at Yzerfontein on the West Coast over the weekend.At least a dozen people have drowned at lagoons and beaches across the Western Cape in the space of a week.The National Sea Rescue Institute s Craig Lambinon says, Police divers are continuing with the search and the family is being assisted by police trauma counselors. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)